    {
      "id": "line-000",
      "start": 0.0,
      "end": 4.64,
      "text": "This is a LibriVox recording. All LibriVox recordings are in the public domain.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-001",
      "start": 5.5,
      "end": 11.02,
      "text": "For more information and to find out how you can volunteer, please visit LibriVox.org.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-002",
      "start": 12.06,
      "end": 14.44,
      "text": "ASOP's Fables, the Nat and the Bull.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-003",
      "start": 15.26,
      "end": 20.36,
      "text": "A Nat alighted on one of the horns of a bull and remained sitting there for considerable time.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-004",
      "start": 21.14,
      "end": 25.02,
      "text": "When it had rested sufficiently and was about to fly away, it said to the bull,",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-005",
      "start": 25.02,
      "end": 30.58,
      "text": "do you mind if I go now? The bull merely raised his eyes and remarked without interest.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-006",
      "start": 31.58,
      "end": 36.18,
      "text": "It's all went to me. I didn't notice when you came and I shan't know when you go away.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-007",
      "start": 37.14,
      "end": 42.02,
      "text": "We may often be of more consequence than our own eyes than in the eyes of our neighbors.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-008",
      "start": 43.5,
      "end": 47.22,
      "text": "And of ASOP's Fable, the Nat and the Bull.",
      "note": ""
    }
  ],
